  fhir:description [ fhir:v "Morphological family grouping codes derived from the CanReg5 MorphFam.txt lookup file. Each morphology code is assigned to a morphological family, which is used in the Sex-Morphology check (to identify rare sex-morphology combinations) and the Topography-Morphology check (to evaluate morphology-topography combinations against MUST and MUST-NOT lookup tables). Code 99 (N/A) indicates the family is accepted with any topography."] ; # 
